description:
Welcome to my studio. It is on first floor. All necessities supplied, including self-served breakfast. Bedding professionally laundried. Close to Central Park. A lot of food, theaters, shopping malls. Subway line 1 only one-minutes walk, you can go anywhere of the Manhattan. Safe neighborhood: Columbia University students here.

This is a standard Manhattan studio, tiny, clean and well decorated.
I treat it as home, study work and welcome friends here.

review.comments: Michael's place was very comfortable.  I really appreciated his honesty in describing it as tiny.  I did not find this to be a problem since I wanted to spend my time enjoying NY and not sitting in the room.  The kitchen was extremely modern and very well equipped.  The living space was more basic but fine.  The TV streamed Netflix & Amazon Prime.  Micheal was very responsive to my requests.  There was some street noise during the night & in the morning but wearing ear plugs took care of that.  Michael was an interesting person to talk to.  The apt. was in a great location - restaurants, interesting food, and convenient transportation.
